The paper focuses on the documentation work in data analytics open source software libraries, which involves a combination of technical and social skills. Therefore, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges and practices of documentation work, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The ethnographic fieldwork and qualitative interviews conducted for the study suggest a focus on human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another likely category. The paper also touches upon information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) in the context of data analytics.
